        {
            "_comment": "Nuvoton NCT6779 Super-I/O HW monitor via its i2c back door (nct6775-i2c at i2c1:0x2d, also declared in the DTS). HwmonTempSensor reads temperature channels only - NOT the chip's voltages or fan tach. Name -> temp1_input, NameN -> temp(N+1)_input; threshold Index = that hwmon temp number. Only the two channels that report trustworthy values are named here: temp1 SYSTIN (board ambient) and temp13 TSI0 (AMD SB-TSI CPU die temp). The rest read garbage on this board: CPUTIN (temp2) is uncalibrated (~98C idle vs 39C actual), AUXTIN0/3 are unconnected, PCH_* (temp7-12) are 0, and TSI1-7 (temp14-20) are absent/garbage. Gated PowerState On because SB-TSI returns nonsense (not an error) when the host is off.",
            "Address": "0x2D",
            "Bus": 1,
            "Name": "SYSTIN",
            "Name12": "CPU SB-TSI",
            "PowerState": "On",
            "Thresholds": [
                {"Index": 1,  "Direction": "greater than", "Name": "upper non critical", "Severity": 0, "Value": 60},
                {"Index": 1,  "Direction": "greater than", "Name": "upper critical",     "Severity": 1, "Value": 70},
                {"Index": 13, "Direction": "greater than", "Name": "upper non critical", "Severity": 0, "Value": 85},
                {"Index": 13, "Direction": "greater than", "Name": "upper critical",     "Severity": 1, "Value": 95}
            ],
            "Type": "NCT6779"
